
!begindoc


!title Use html on a EBook Reader (Linux)
!maketitle

!= Settings of PC (BSD)
Create a document with C.UTF-8. 

!| nconfig set locale 



!= MRK Document
Create the document using mrk markup.
It can be converted to html with the command

!| 
!| bsdhtml test.mrk 
!|

A file with html extension will be produced. 

On the EBook reader, the html file will be easily opened.
It can be read easily with special chars, using C.UTF-8
in settings of the EBook reader.


!enddoc
 






